orwegian people of Danish descent]]\n[[Category:Paus family]]\n[[Category:People from Skien]]\n", "name_user": "124.183.202.90", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEarly life and family)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henrik_Ibsen"}
{"title_page": "Bogor railway station", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name = Bogor Station\n| native_name = <small>''Stasiun Bogor''</small>\n| native_name_lang = id\n| image = Bogor Station.jpg\n| image_caption = Bogor Station\n| address = Jalan Nyi Raja Permas No.1 bogor 16124, Central Bogor<br>[[Bogor]]\n| country = [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|-6.5942707|106.7908108|format=dms|region:ID_type:railwaystation|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation = {{convert|246|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| line = <!-- line information is detailed under \"services\" -->\n| other = \n| platform = 6 [[bay platform]]s\n| tracks = 8\n| parking = Available\n| bicycle = \n| baggage_check = \n| passengers = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| pass_system = \n| opened = 1881\n| rebuilt = \n| ADA = Available\n| code = BOO\n| owned = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n| operator = [[KA Commuter Jabodetabek]]\n| zone = \n| services = {{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n                       {{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bogor-Jakarta Kota|previous=|next=Cilebut|rows1=2}}\n                       {{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bogor-Jatinegara|previous=|next=Cilebut|hide1=true}}\n| structure = Ground\n}}\n\n'''Bogor Station''' ('''BOO''') is a [[train station]] located in the city of [[Bogor]], [[West Java]]. This station serves as the terminus for [[KA Commuter Line Jakarta Kota\u2013Bogor|Red Line]] and [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara\u2013Bogor|Yellow Line]] services of [[KRL Commuterline]]. The station has five [[island platform]]s and two [[side platform]]s. The station is located 246 meter [[above sea level]].\n\nThe station was first commissioned as the terminus for Jakarta-Buitenzorg (Bogor's previous name) service in 1872. The current building was built in 1881. It was built in the style of [[Neoclassical architecture]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Stasiun Bogor |url=https://heritage.kai.id/page/Stasiun%20Bogor |website=PT Kereta Api Indonesia (Persero) (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref> In 20 October 2016, KRL Commuterline unveiled a new 570 square meter hall built in front of the station. This expansion was built mainly to maximize the passenger flow and to separate both incoming and outgoing passengers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lebih Luas, Hall Baru Stasiun Bogor Mulai Dioperasikan |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/814117/lebih-luas-hall-baru-stasiun-bogor-mulai-dioperasikan |website=Tempo (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Perluasan Hall Stasiun Bogor Bentuk Peningkatan Layanan PT KCJ Bagi Pengguna Commuter Line |url=http://www.krl.co.id/perluasan-hall-stasiun-bogor-bentuk-peningkatan-layanan-pt-kcj-bagi-pengguna-commuter-line/ |website=krl.co.id (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThis station used to serve intercity trains. Nowadays, the intercity services have moved from this station to the nearby [[Bogor Paledang railway station|Bogor Paledang station]].\n\n==Services==\n===Commuter lines===\n*{{rint|jakarta|red}}  [[KA Commuter Line Jakarta Kota\u2013Bogor]]\n*{{rint|jakarta|yellow}}  [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara\u2013Bogor]]\n\n==Places of Interest==\n*[[Bogor Botanical Gardens]]\n*[[Bogor Palace]]\n*Museum Nasional Sejarah Alam Indonesia (Indonesian Museum of Ethnobotany)\n*Museum Perjuangan Bogor (Bogor Perjuangan Museum)\n*[[Pembela Tanah Air Museum]]\n*[[Bogor Agricultural University]] Baranangsiang Campus\n*[[Jagorawi Toll Road]] Bogor Toll Gate\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Bogor Station}}\n\n{{s-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Cilebut}}\n|route    = [[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Manggarai\u2013Padalarang</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Bogor Paledang}}\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Manggarai}}\n|term2    = {{stnlnk|Padalarang}}\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{KA Commuter Jabodetabek stations}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|West Java}}\n\n[[category:Bogor]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in West Java]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1881]]\n[[Category:1881 establishments in the Dutch Empire]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name = Bogor Station\n| native_name = <small>''Stasiun Bogor''</small>\n| native_name_lang = id\n| image = Bogor Station.jpg\n| image_caption = Bogor Station\n| address = Jalan Nyi Raja Permas No.1 bogor 16124, Central Bogor<br>[[Bogor]]\n| country = [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|-6.5942707|106.7908108|format=dms|region:ID_type:railwaystation|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation = {{convert|246|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| line = <!-- line information is detailed under \"services\" -->\n| other = \n| platform = 6 [[bay platform]]s\n| tracks = 8\n| parking = Available\n| bicycle = \n| baggage_check = \n| passengers = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| pass_system = \n| opened = 1881\n| rebuilt = \n| ADA = Available\n| code = BOO\n| owned = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n| operator = [[KA Commuter Jabodetabek]]\n| zone = \n| services = {{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n                       {{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bogor-Jakarta Kota|previous=|next=Cilebut|rows1=2}}\n                       {{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bogor-Jatinegara|previous=|next=Cilebut|hide1=true}}\n| structure = Ground\n}}\n\n'''Bogor Station''' ('''BOO''') is a [[train station]] located in the city of [[Bogor]], [[West Java]]. This station serves as the terminus for [[KA Commuter Line Jakarta Kota\u2013Bogor|Red Line]] and [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara\u2013Bogor|Yellow Line]] services of [[KRL Commuterline]]. The station has five [[island platform]]s and two [[side platform]]s. The station is located 246 meter [[above sea level]].\n\nThe station was first commissioned as the terminus for Jakarta-Buitenzorg (Bogor's previous name) service in 1872. The current building was built in 1881. It was built in the style of [[Neoclassical architecture]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Stasiun Bogor |url=https://heritage.kai.id/page/Stasiun%20Bogor |website=PT Kereta Api Indonesia (Persero) (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref> In 20 October 2016, KRL Commuterline unveiled a new 570 square meter hall built in front of the station. This expansion was built mainly to maximize the passenger flow and to separate both incoming and outgoing passengers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lebih Luas, Hall Baru Stasiun Bogor Mulai Dioperasikan |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/814117/lebih-luas-hall-baru-stasiun-bogor-mulai-dioperasikan |website=Tempo (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Perluasan Hall Stasiun Bogor Bentuk Peningkatan Layanan PT KCJ Bagi Pengguna Commuter Line |url=http://www.krl.co.id/perluasan-hall-stasiun-bogor-bentuk-peningkatan-layanan-pt-kcj-bagi-pengguna-commuter-line/ |website=krl.co.id (in Indonesian) |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThis station used to serve intercity trains. Nowadays, the intercity services have moved from this station to the nearby [[Bogor Paledang railway station|Bogor Paledang station]].\n\n==Services==\n===Commuter lines===\n*{{rint|jakarta|red}}  [[KA Commuter Line Jakarta Kota\u2013Bogor]]\n*{{rint|jakarta|yellow}}  [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara\u2013Bogor]]\n\n==Places of Interest==\n*[[Bogor Botanical Gardens]]\n*[[Bogor Palace]]\n*Museum Nasional Sejarah Alam Indonesia (Indonesian Museum of Ethnobotany)\n*Museum Perjuangan Bogor (Bogor Perjuangan Museum)\n*[[Pembela Tanah Air Museum]]\n*[[Bogor Agricultural University]] Baranangsiang Campus\n*[[Jagorawi Toll Road]] Bogor Toll Gate\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Bogor Station}}\n\n{{s-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Cilebut}}\n|route    = [[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<